Ledgerium AI — MVP Overview

Ledgerium AI helps you capture how work actually gets done and turn it into clear, usable process documentation—automatically.

1. Sidebar Workflow Recorder (Chrome Extension)

Ledgerium starts with a lightweight sidebar that lives inside your browser.
You click “Start Recording,” perform your normal workflow, and click “Stop.”

That’s it.

No workshops. No interviews. No guessing.

The recorder quietly captures privacy-safe signals about your actions—like clicks, navigation, and interactions—without storing sensitive content. It shows you exactly what’s being recorded so you stay in control.

2. Workflow JSON + Event Data

Behind the scenes, your session is turned into a structured workflow JSON file.

This file contains:

A timeline of your actions
The systems and pages you used
The sequence of steps you took
Clean, normalized event data (not raw keystrokes or sensitive inputs)

Think of it as a precise, portable record of how the process actually happened—not how someone thinks it happens.

3. Deterministic Process Engine

The JSON file is then processed by Ledgerium’s Deterministic Process Engine.

This engine:

Converts raw event data into meaningful workflow steps
Groups actions into logical activities
Builds a structured process flow
Generates clear outputs you can actually use

From a single recording, Ledgerium produces:

Process Map
A visual flow of the workflow showing each step in order.

Operational Definitions
Clear explanations of what each step is, what it does, and how it fits into the process.

Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)
A structured, step-by-step guide based on what actually happened—not assumptions.

Why this matters

Most process documentation is based on memory, opinion, or outdated SOPs.

Ledgerium AI is based on evidence.

You record the work once, and immediately get:

A baseline of the real process
Clear documentation of how it actually runs
A reusable foundation for improvement, training, or handoff

No friction. No guesswork. Just a clean, accurate view of reality.
